    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-03-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-03-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="238"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d238">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Sir <persName
                            type="to">Julian Pauncefote</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-03-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 356.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Referring to previous correspondence
                    concerning the claim of James Bain against the United States, I have the honor
                    to inform you that the case was referred to the Committee on Foreign Affairs of
                    the House of Representatives on the 27th ultimo, with a favorable recommendation
                    from this Department, and the additional facts contained in your note of the 23d
                    instant have to-day been communicated to the committee.</p>
                <p>As soon as the determination of the committee is known it will be communicated to
                    you.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
